race.comment: ZOURAIN (2) resumes. He's a talented type who was running well in some decent 3yo races last time in. The 1200m is going to be a bit short of his best but this looks a winnable race and he draws for every chance. MERCURIAL LADY (8) did enough fresh at Moonee Valley over this trip, battling home for fifth. She's another that we think will be better suited over a bit further but she should strip fitter and the bigger track will suit. REGAL MIGHT (4) was poor last time in a strong race at Sandown Hillside but the fresh effort was good and he could bounce back. DOLLAR CHASER (3) ran well fresh and should be fighting out the finish from a good draw.
